Account and Security-IAM Identity and Access Management:
-------------------------------------------------------
IAM nothing but who can access AWS services and what they can do ?
User ---> Permission ----> Aws Service
IAM Like security for AWS

Root user and IAM User ?
------------------------
Root user:
-The Account created when you first sing up for AWS
-Root user Full access to EVERYTHING
-Cannot be restricted
-One per account
-Root user can create IAM user
-Root user create IAM user and grant specific persmission like (Ec2 access, S3 access, Database access etc)
-Root can add or revoke permission any time for IAM user also can delete IAM user any time

Note: Root user is like admin of admin -- should not used daily

IAM User:
-A user created inside the AWS for daily work
-IAM user has limited access (bases on policies)
-Multiple users can exist
-Controlled permission

Note: IAM users are for developers and Technical engineers

REAL-LIFE EXAMPLE:
------------------
Root User --> Company owner ---> IAM user ---> Employees

What Not To DO?
---------------
Use root user for Development, CI/CD, Daily login etc

Best Practices:
---------------
Root User:
Root user Enable MFA
Do not use daily
Keep credentials safe

IAM User:
Assing least privilege
Use roles where possible
Rotate keys

Note:
Root user has full access and should only be used for account setup. IAM users have controlled permission and are used for daily operations.


Core Components:
----------------
1.Users : Indiivual person or application
Ex: DevOps engineer or Developer

2.Groups :
Collection of Users
Ex: Dev Team or Admin team

3.Policies :
JSON Rules that define persmission

Note: polices define what action are allowed or denied

4.Roles :
Temporary access (no login required)
used  --> S3 access
lambda ---> DB access

Note:roles are used by services, not people

IAM Structure:
--------------
User --> Group ---> Policy ---> AWS access


Types of AWS access:
---------------------
1.Console : Username + Password + MFA
2.Programmatic : Access key + secret key













